This paper is about building dialog systems using data-driven approaches, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural seq2seq architectures, which is a popular technique in deep learning and falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper includes human evaluations and discusses the design of dialog systems, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper presents a new dataset, which could also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
